COPY public.testimonials (id, community_id, author_name, author_relation, content, rating, featured, approved, sort_order, created_at, updated_at, highlight, image_id) FROM stdin;
28b46534-b723-4fe3-a1c5-36ff30fa9601	b2c48ce7-11cb-4216-afdb-f2429ccae81f	Jennifer Thompson	Daughter	The Gardens on Quail exceeded all our expectations. The custom design and upscale amenities made Mom feel like she was moving to a resort, not a care facility. The bistro food is restaurant quality and the theater events keep her engaged. Worth every penny.	5	t	t	1	2025-09-23 22:11:14.024418	2025-09-23 22:11:14.024418	\N	\N
7c35186d-756c-4d91-9fd5-b4767dea51c8	b2c48ce7-11cb-4216-afdb-f2429ccae81f	Michael Rodriguez	Husband	My wife has been in memory care here for 6 months. The specialized programming and family story sessions have helped preserve her sense of self. The staff truly understands memory care - it's not just about safety, it's about maintaining dignity and joy.	5	t	t	2	2025-09-23 22:11:14.024418	2025-09-23 22:11:14.024418	\N	\N
c7080855-fe8b-41d0-b0c4-4cdf7b736093	ac9dae44-d18f-4e96-b3bf-ba3d4fc406e9	Patricia Wilson	Daughter	Golden Pond has been locally owned for over 20 years and it shows in every interaction. They know each resident personally and the 98% satisfaction rate is well-deserved. Dad feels at home here and we have peace of mind knowing he's in good hands.	5	t	t	1	2025-09-23 22:11:35.105796	2025-09-23 22:11:35.105796	\N	\N
6e82a066-7743-423c-90f7-f132a247c08e	ac9dae44-d18f-4e96-b3bf-ba3d4fc406e9	James Anderson	Son	The value at Golden Pond is unmatched in the Golden area. All-inclusive pricing means no surprise bills, and the mountain views from Dad's apartment are beautiful. Staff turnover is low which means consistent, caring relationships.	5	t	t	2	2025-09-23 22:11:35.105796	2025-09-23 22:11:35.105796	\N	\N
b6586b8e-d19b-4fee-bdc8-f771564be96a	d20c45d3-8201-476a-aeb3-9b941f717ccf	Maria Garcia	Daughter	The "Your Story First" approach at Stonebridge isn't just marketing - they really live it. The family story sessions helped them understand Mom's history and preferences. Now her care plan reflects who she really is, not just her medical needs.	5	t	t	1	2025-09-23 22:11:35.105796	2025-09-23 22:11:35.105796	\N	\N
04244839-eab9-43e0-a308-a0709c9ca9f0	d20c45d3-8201-476a-aeb3-9b941f717ccf	David Johnson	Son	Since the renovation, Stonebridge has become a beautiful, modern community while keeping the personal touch. The staff remembers Dad's stories and treats him as an individual. That means everything to our family.	5	t	t	2	2025-09-23 22:11:35.105796	2025-09-23 22:11:35.105796	\N	\N
6ae68c4c-1aa4-4cc8-a038-ee30ddc2a7ea	dea2cbbe-32da-4774-a85b-5dd9286892ed	Susan Martinez	Daughter	Mom has been at The Gardens at Columbine for 8 months now and the change has been incredible. She went from being isolated at home to having a full social calendar. The memory care team knows her story and treats her with such dignity. The gardens really do make a difference - she spends hours there every day.	5	t	t	1	2025-09-23 22:11:14.024418	2025-09-23 22:11:14.024418	\N	\N
57d8b6df-289f-488e-a97d-ebe56cb4dc82	dea2cbbe-32da-4774-a85b-5dd9286892ed	Robert Chen	Son	Dad was hesitant about moving to assisted living, but the staff at Gardens at Columbine made the transition so smooth. They really listen to what residents want and need. The 2+ acre gardens give him the outdoor space he loves, and the care is exceptional.	5	t	t	2	2025-09-23 22:11:14.024418	2025-09-23 22:11:14.024418	\N	\N
\.


